{"lemma":"سُبُلِ","slug":"سُبُلِ","root":"س.ب.ل","root_slug":"س-ب-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ب-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَبِيل","root":"سبل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":176},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18815","n18816"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way, path, road"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manner, method"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ways and means"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kinship"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"necessary connection"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"distribution of water"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"public fountain"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"blame","examples":[{"text":"إِنَّمَا السَّبِيلُ عَلَى الَّذِينَ يَظْلِمُونَ النَّاسَ وَيَبْغُونَ فِي الْأَرْضِ بِغَيْرِ الْحَقِّ ۚ أُولَٰئِكَ لَهُمْ عَذَابٌ أَلِيمٌ","english":"The blame is only against the ones who wrong the people and tyrannize upon the earth without right. Those will have a painful punishment."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root س ب ل (s b l). Given the frequent religious usage of the word, there is some semantic interference of the Classical Syriac ܫܒܝܠܐ (šəbīlā). Cognate to Aramaic שְׁבִילׇא (šəḇīlā), Hebrew שְׁבִיל (šəḇī́l, “trail, path”)."},"ipa":["/sa.biːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18815","headword_ar":"سَبَلٌ","root":"sbl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that one has let loose, let down, let fall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made to hang down, and to drag"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the ground"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na$arN","text_ar":"نَشَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ a thing that one has spread ” &c.: whence the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano jar~a","text_ar":"مَنْ جَرَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalahu mina AlxuyalaA='i laA yanoZuru A@ll~`hu yawoma Alqiy`mapi","text_ar":"سَبَلَهُ مِنَ الخُيَلَا=ءِ لَا يَنْظُرُ ا@للّٰهُ يَوْمَ القِيٰمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who drags what he has made to hang down"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his garment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from pride,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self-conceit, God will not look towards him on the day of resurrection"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalN","text_ar":"سَبَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments made to hang down"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to drag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalapN","text_ar":"سَبَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [or rather a coll. gen. n. of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalapN","text_ar":"سَبَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.;] whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jar~a sabalatahu","text_ar":"جَرَّ سَبَلَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) which means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dragged his garment;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though said to mean,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his garments."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain issuing from the clouds and not as yet having reached the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 359.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, app., as indicating swiftness,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalu","text_ar":"سَبَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excellent mare, said"},{"kind":"text","text":"by As"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to have been the mother of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and to have belonged to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tribe of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ghanee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalN","text_ar":"سَبَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalu","text_ar":"سَبَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a fem. proper name] is a name for (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such is called to be milked by saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalo sabalo","text_ar":"سَبَلْ سَبَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ibn-'Abbád, TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) which signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ears of corn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA: [and in like manner both are expl. in the KL, but as singulars, app. because used as gen. ns.:]) n. un. of the former with ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and so of ↓ the latter: and the pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"funoEulN","text_ar":"فُنْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanaAbilu","text_ar":"سَنَابِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulapN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulaAtN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kur xii. 43 and 46:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulapN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK (erroneously)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subolap","text_ar":"سُبْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ear of corn"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so I render"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaroEapN","text_ar":"زَرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuroEap","text_ar":"زُرْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is bending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuwlapN","text_ar":"سَبُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned in one of my two copies of the S as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulapN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"but not in the other copy] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwlapN","text_ar":"سُبُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalapN","text_ar":"سَبَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or, accord. to Lth, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabuwlapN","text_ar":"سَبُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ear"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulap","text_ar":"سُنْبُلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of millet"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*urap","text_ar":"ذُرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, when bending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA:) and some say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalN","text_ar":"سَبَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spreading,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expanding, awn of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobul","text_ar":"سُنْبُل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ears of corn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (M, TA;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremities thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"subuwlN","text_ar":"سُبُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbwl","text_ar":"سبول"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulN","text_ar":"سُنْبُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the dial. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnw hmyAn","text_ar":"بنو هميان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[?]. (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~unobulapu","text_ar":"السُّنْبُلَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain sign of the Zodiac"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Virgo"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S in the present art., and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"snbl","text_ar":"سنبل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spica Virginis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a star in Virgo; thus called by astrologers; also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imaAku AlA^aEozalu","text_ar":"السِّمَاكُ الاَعْزَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kzw. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smk","text_ar":"سمك"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iybi","text_ar":"الطِّيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulu","text_ar":"سُنْبُلُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spikenard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is called in the present day"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~unobulu AlhinodiY~u","text_ar":"السُّنْبُلُ الهِنْدِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brought from India."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"snbl","text_ar":"سنبل"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  Also sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaAlN","text_ar":"اَسْبَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bucket, (O,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lips"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (S:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalapN","text_ar":"سَبَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaAlN","text_ar":"اَسْبَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in these senses; and signifies (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a vessel [like as it signifies the “ ear, ” which is the “ head, ” of a culm of wheat &c.]. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaA^ahaA A_ilaY A^asobaAlihaA","text_ar":"مَلَاَهَا اـِلَى اَسْبَالِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. the winecup,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkaA^osa","text_ar":"الكَاْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, TA, or the bucket,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~alowa","text_ar":"الدَّلْوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its edges,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to its lips."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And a poet says, (S,) namely Bá'ith Ibn- Sureym El-Yeshkuree, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*o A^arosaluwniY maAtiHFA bidilaAy^ihimo\n                      \n                     \n                        famalaA^otuhuA EalaqFA A_ilaY A^asobaAlihaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When they sent me drawing with their buckets, and I filled them with blood to their brims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he says, they sent me seeking to execute their blood-revenges, and I slew many:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEalaq","text_ar":"العَلَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1302},{"kind":"text","text":"“ blood. ” (S, TA. [See also Ham p. 268, where some different readings are mentioned; and it is said that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsbAl","text_ar":"اسبال"},{"kind":"text","text":"may mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knots that are connected with the cross-pieces of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the bucket.]) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A number of spears, few"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [Perhaps because their heads are likened to the heads of corn.])       -A3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sibaAlN","text_ar":"سِبَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the Moheet. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arogama A@ll~`hu sabalahu","text_ar":"اَرْغَمَ ا@للّٰهُ سَبَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make his nose to cleave to the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abase,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"humble, him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Garments made of the hards,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hurds, of flax of the coarsest of qualities:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalapN","text_ar":"سَبَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[if one of these words be not a mistranscription for the other]. (TA.)       -A5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain disease in the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHu","text_ar":"رِيحُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~abali","text_ar":"السَّبَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. in the M,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling a film, as though it were the web of a spider, with red veins:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a film of the eye, from the swelling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inflation, of its external veins upon the surface of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulotaHimap","text_ar":"مُلْتَحِمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which is one of the layers of the eye, (TA,) [namely, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tunica albuginea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white of the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in the present day,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the appearance of a web,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing woven, between the two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between those veins and the white tunic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like smoke:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a film covering the eye;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isobaAlo","text_ar":"اـِسْبَالْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the “ letting down ” of a veil, or curtain. (Mgh.)       -A6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A reviling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vilifying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoniY wa bayonahu sabalN","text_ar":"بَيْنِى وَ بَيْنَهُ سَبَلٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between me and him is a reviling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vilifying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Moheet. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","TA","S","M","K","AZ","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n18816","headword_ar":"سَبِلٌ","root":"sbl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[is app. a possessive epithet, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having length and flaccidity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuSoyapN sabilapN","text_ar":"خُصْيَةٌ سَبِلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A scrotum"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is long"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and flaccid."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}